One year after the carnival-like burial ceremony that brought the businessman, Obi Cubana into limelight, he remembered his mother, Ezinne Uche Iyiegbu. The burial ceremony at Oba Anambra State, which ran for a week, was the topic of discussion online and offline as it witnessed displays of affluence. Over 200 cows were slaughtered, assorted foods laid out on tables, tonnes of expensive wine and spirit downed by hundreds of relations, friends, associates and well-wishers plus, the Cubana CEO replicated his late mother’s face with gemstones worth $100,000.   Fela, Keith Richards inspired my career – Highlife Soes     There’s still hope for Nigeria – Davido     Story of Jesus death, resurrection manipulative – Amber Rose   Twelve months after laying his mother to rest, Obi Cubana expressed love and appreciated her for the love she imbibed in his siblings and himself The nightlife boss promised they’ll never disappoint their late parents “It’s been a year mama. We love you, we miss you, we thank God for the love u imbibed in us while you were here. “We will NEVER let you and papa down. Keep resting till we meet to part no more. #odoziakaeze2021,” he wrote.